{
  "The US federal income tax system is best described as:": "",
  "Regressive — lower earners pay a higher percentage": "",
  "Voluntary — taxpayers choose their own rate": "",
  "Flat — everyone pays the same percentage": "",
  "Progressive — higher portions of income are taxed at increasingly higher rates": "",
  "The US federal income tax uses a progressive structure where successive portions of income are taxed at higher marginal rates, so higher earners pay a larger percentage on their top dollars.": "",
  "In a progressive tax system, moving into a higher tax bracket means:": "",
  "You will take home less money overall": "",
  "All your income is taxed at the new higher rate": "",
  "Your previous bracket rate increases as well": "",
  "Only the income above the bracket threshold is taxed at the higher rate": "",
  "Only the income that falls within the new bracket is taxed at the higher marginal rate. Income in lower brackets continues to be taxed at those lower rates.": "",
