  "Sandra earns $65,000 and is deciding between contributing $6,500 to a traditional IRA (tax-deductible now, taxed on withdrawal) or a Roth IRA (no deduction now, tax-free withdrawal). She is currently in the 22% bracket and expects to be in the 12% bracket in retirement. Which choice saves her more in total lifetime taxes?": "",
